The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                An unclaimed motorcycle parked in front of South City mall on Prince Anwar Shah Road triggered panic on Monday evening. A ticking sound from the vehicle led to a bomb scare. The security guards at the mall checked the vehicle with metal detectors and informed Jadavpur police station when they could not locate the source of the sound.   ehicular movement was stopped on the stretch of Prince Anwar Shah Road in front of the mall for around 40 minutes. Later, police officers said there was no bomb inside the motorcycle.    A 45-year-old resident of Shibpur was found unconscious in the red-light area of Sonagachhi early on Monday. Residents said Mohammad Istiak had visited a sex worker on Sunday afternoon and fallen asleep in her room around 3pm. When he did not get up after almost 12 hours, residents took him to hospital, where he was declared dead. Police have started an investigation and sent the body for post-mortem.    Sheikh Akhtar, 30, of Fatakpur village, died after a speeding lorry knocked him down at the Circular Garden Reach Road and Hyde Road crossing on Monday morning. He was taken to SSKM Hospital, where he died. The lorry driver has been arrested.    Sourav Saha, a resident of Thakurpukur, was arrested on Monday in connection with the attack on journalists and cameramen in Behala on Friday morning. The youth in his 20s was granted bail by an Alipore court later in the day.   ournalists alleged that Saha had kicked one of them in the stomach. The journalists have submitted a memorandum to the district superintendent of police (south), Ajey Ranade, demanding the arrest of all those involved in Fridays attack.    City police and the civic authorities inspected Nandaram market on Monday to make a list of the parts that have been declared illegal by the Supreme Court and later unsafe by the fire and emergency services department. Mayor Bikash Ranjan Bhattacharyya had asked the civic building department to demolish the illegal and unsafe parts of the market with the help of the police.    Jeetu Das, 42, and Geeta Dey, 40, were arrested on Monday for trying to snatch a gold chain from a woman at a fair in Lake Town.   olice said Das pushed the woman, a resident of Kalindi, and Dey snatched the chain. The duo then tried to flee but the woman raised an alarm and they were caught by shopkeepers.            
